{
  "texts": [
    "This technique is especially useful with models, like GPT-4, enabling users to influence model responses without retraining [38].",
    "While we do employ prompt engineering in this paper to provide further context to various pretrained and fine-tuned LLMs, it is not our primary focus, and its discussion will be more limited.",
    "The key point to make about prompt engineering is that it is a useful way to improve performance of LLMs on specific tasks, with or without other refinement methods, and it is often the easiest refinement method to try.",
    "Fine-tuningFine-tuning, often used interchangeably with transfer learning, is the practice of further training a pretrained model on a specific dataset to tailor it for a particular task.",
    "It capitalizes on the model's pre-existing knowledge, enhancing its performance for specialized tasks and often resulting in better accuracy, even with limited data."
  ]
}